defaultCompetition Law
default3.39
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOfcom undertakes competition law investigations 
defaultin the communications sector 
defaultunder two parallel provisions, the Compe
defaulttition Act 1998, and the Treaty for the Functioning of the European Union (TFEU), which concerns 
defaultissues affecting 
defaulttrade between EU member states. Both provisions describe two broadly similar forms of behaviour that can be subject to investigation under com
defaultpetition law.
default3.40
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe first form of behaviour (prohibited under Chapter I of the Competition Act and Article 101 of the TFEU) is when parties enter into anti-competitive agreements that prevent, restrict or distort competition. One example of such behaviour wo
defaultuld be the operation of a cartel. 
default3.41
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe second form of behaviour (prohibited under Chapter II of the Competition Act and Article 102 of the TFEU) is conduct that amounts to an abuse of a dominant position. Having a dominant position is not against the law i
defaultn itself, and it is only when this dominant position is abused that we would find a party in breach of 
defaultcompetition law. Examples of an abuse of a dominant position include, but are not limited to, excessive pricing, price discrimination, refusal to supply,
default predatory pricing and margin squeeze. 
default3.42
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe BBC is subject to both forms of prohibition under competition law.
default3.43
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOfcom also has the power to make market investigation references under the Enterprise Act 2002. Ofcom exercises all these powers concurrently wit
defaulth the Office of Fair Trading (soon to
default 
defaultbe the Competition and Markets Authority). 
defaultInformation on Ofcom’s approach to competition law inve
defaultstigations can be found in our enforcement g
defaultuidelines
default.
defaultBroadcasting Act licences
