defaultes from Ofcom under the Broadcasting Acts 1990 and 1996. Under the Communications Act, Ofcom has powers to impose conditions in those licences to: 
defaulta)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultensure fair and effective competition in the provision of broadcast services; and
default;
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultensure compliance with a 
defaultCode for practices to be followed in the provision of electronic programme guides. 
default&#xa0;
default3.45
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe may also open an investigation into whether or not the relevant licence condition has been breached. Before 
defaultexercising powers under 
defaultlicence condition
defaults
default 
defaultin relation to a 
defaultcompetition issue
